    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 20</em>, <em>PRPG Core Rulebook pg. 143</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 90 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 10 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6/1d6 (small), 1d8/1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> B; <strong>Special</strong> disarm, double, trip</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Double; Flails</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>A dire flail consists of two spheres of spiked iron dangling from chains at opposite ends of a long haft. This weapon excels at short but powerful strikes, and is typically swung in a constant churning motion. The wielder of a dire flail must have great strength, both to use the weapon effectively and to keep from tiring out.</p>",
